[normal]E)[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]T[bold]he effect of competi[bold]tion between accreditation bodies, and the two separate registers of electricians, on the standards of review of dome[bold]s[bold]tic electrical work; [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]5.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Competition between accreditation bodies has a number of effects. Lowering standards to compete is not something NA
[normal]PIT have subscribed to as we believe that many competent electricians reject this approach. 
[normal]5.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Any tendency to lower standards is 
[normal]already 
[normal]being counteracted by the 
[normal]condition that all CPS providers adhere to the revised EAS document (2012)
[normal] which includes higher standards
[normal]. NAPIT believe this will 
[normal]mitigate any 
[normal]opportunity 
[normal]for s
[normal]tandards to be lowered,
[normal] as those who do so 
[normal]after June 2014
[normal] 
[normal]will 
[normal]have their DCLG auth
[normal]orisation revoked
[normal]. 
[normal]5.3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Another negative aspect of competition wh
[normal]ich has been seen in th
[normal]e past was
[normal] “scheme
[normal] provider
[normal] hopping
[normal]”, where a member of 
[normal]a scheme could be excluded, but then join another scheme and carry on working even though they were not deemed to be able to do so by a previous CPS provider
[normal]. 
[normal]T
[normal]his is already being addressed by CPS pr
[normal]oviders in line with point 14 of DCLGs new conditions of authorisation
[normal].
[normal]5.4
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The other side of this argument is that competition gives electrician’s choice. If they are unhappy with a particular aspect of a scheme, they are able to vote with their feet and mov
[normal]e to another.  
[normal]NAPIT believe this is very positive for the provision of the competent person scheme 
[normal]in general 
[normal]as it prevents providers from becoming complacent and enco
[normal]ur
[normal]ages them to provide 
[normal]an efficient service that also represents value for money
[normal].
[normal] This
[normal] has encouraged scheme providers to 
[normal]offer their members more
[normal] services
[normal] and was one of the factors that influenced NAPITs
[normal] Complete Solution approach
[normal], an approach which enables our
[normal] members to more easily and cost effectively 
[normal]notify work across multiple work a
[normal]reas
[normal] which they have demonstrated competence in
[normal]. 
[normal]5.5
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The introduction of DCLG Conditions of Authorisation have standardised requirements for all CPS providers. This means that standards and the quality of review will all have to comply with the high standards
[normal] set out in DCLG requirements by June 2014. The introduction of such standardisation means that only the positive aspects of competition remain. 
