[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]One key element of accreditation is that EN45011 requires an independent committee (sometimes called an impartiality committee, 
[normal]in NAPIT’s case it
[normal]s Governing Board) who independently review the operations of a scheme operator, make recommendations as they see fit, and have the power to report the scheme operator to UKAS or the Department if their advice is not followed. DCLG requir
[normal]e this to be in place by June 2014 but NAPIT’s Governing Board has been in place since 2009 and has been found to be of great value in helping us to identify and deliver real improvements to the benefit of scheme members, consumers and the government.
